pageContext.description: Conical socket. Very flat wings of even thickness and very narrow slight bevel. Blade broken and cracked in one place. Two rivet holes in same plane as blade. There is a ridge extending along the seams of the casting which gives a keel like appearance to the sides of the shank. A simple zigzag double line in each of the angles between the wings and the blade.
pageContext.patina: Bright green patina and some dark brown
pageContext.surface: Fairly smooth. The blade more than the shaft is marked and grained in lines longitudinally. Also there are transverse hair-like lines on one aide along the summit of midrib and surrounding the whole shank.
pageContext.publications: Prehistoric Bronzes, 154. No catalogue.,Foster Bequest, 281. The numbers do not correspond in the catalogue.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology, Cambridge,(From Fenton and Sons, 12 Holywell St. WC),z.4301
